Authorship and provenance

All prose, documentation, and source code in this skill were authored
independently by Eluu Labs. The methodology it describes (claim-led titles,
deck-profile routing, a column/baseline grid, measured text fitting, font
embedding, a layout-quality gate, and native Google Slides assembly) reflects
general, widely-practised presentation-design and software-engineering
techniques. No third-party proprietary text, configuration, or code is included
or redistributed here.

This skill targets open, broadly-available tooling only:

  - python-pptx           (MIT License)        — editable .pptx generation
  - Pillow                (HPND / MIT-CMU)     — text metrics and image work
  - matplotlib            (PSF-based License)  — chart rendering
  - LibreOffice (soffice) (MPL-2.0, external)  — rendering/PDF export at runtime
  - Google Slides API     (Google APIs)        — native Slides assembly

These dependencies are used as-is at runtime and are not redistributed by this
skill. Each remains under its own license.
